snippet.textDisplay: Abdul Hannan is lost and depressed, and he chooses to be alone and not go near the crowded street where Kaavish is about to perform. He wanders off into darkness with his thoughts and meets a woman who offers him a flower, a symbol of love and hope; he takes it but he is still worn out and lost in his own world till he hears Kaavish sing so he pauses to listen. The end shot where he is humming Kaavish's bit is the hope you finally see in him
